If it wasn't for the way that the restaurant is on the outside, you would probably pass right by this gem. The restaurant is very unassuming and I'm happy about that because they let their food speak for itself. It has been a few times that I've been here and this day I came with some coworkers... word of advise, come early if you want to get a table cause this place gets packed! We each ordered something different but I went with my good ole stand by of Pad Thai! I love the flavor of this dish and My Thai sure knows how to make it. The portions are large but I'm okay with that because I love to have leftovers of it for later. Pad Thai is one of those foods that I can have everyday... and I'm so glad that this little gem of a restaurant is down the block from my job and the prices aren't out of this world. Looking forward to coming back... oh yum!
For what its worth, the atmosphere and food quality were imo well balanced with the prices, which for downtown Chicago is saying something.
